sentences: Scott Spencer Storch (born December 16, 1973) is an American record producer and songwriter.

Some publications have written that Storch was born in Canada, but in 2010 the Miami New Times wrote a denial under the title "Scott Storch is not Canadian."
Scott Storch began his professional music career in 1991, when he became one of the first members of the hip hop group the Roots as a keyboard player.
Storch was also awarded ASCAP's Songwriter of the Year award in 2006.
